        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-need-a",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best interface is no interface. The second best is one so obvious you forget it exists.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "ux",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-interface-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Nobody has ever complained that something was too easy to use.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "ux",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 2,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "based-nobody-has-ever-complained",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The worst part about being a senior developer isn't the complexity. It's knowing that the simple solution you proposed was right all along.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "senior",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-worst-part-about",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Code that's easy to delete is better than code that's easy to write.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "deletion"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-code-thats-easy-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best code is no code at all. Every line of code is a liability.",
      "author": "Jeff Atwood",
      "author_slug": "atwood",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "less-code"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "atwood-the-best-code-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Simplicity is a prerequisite for reliability.",
      "author": "Edsger W. Dijkstra",
      "author_slug": "dijkstra",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "reliability"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "dijkstra-simplicity-is-a-prerequisite",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The function of good software is to make the complex appear to be simple.",
      "author": "Grady Booch",
      "author_slug": "booch",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "abstraction"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "booch-the-function-of-good",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best engineers aren't the ones who write the most code. They're the ones who delete the most code.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deletion",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-engineers-arent",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your system design document should fit on one page. If it doesn't, your system design is too complicated.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "system-design",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-system-design-document",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you can't explain it to a six-year-old, you don't understand it. If your code can't be read by a junior dev, you haven't simplified it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "clarity",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-cant-explain",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best marketing advice is free. Ship something great and tell people about it. Everything else is optimization.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "marketing"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "marketing",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-marketing-advice",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best SaaS businesses are boring. They solve one problem really well and charge monthly for it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas",
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "saas",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-saas-businesses",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best feature is the one you don't build. Every feature is a future maintenance burden and a current cognitive load.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "users",
        "product",
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "features",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-feature-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best code you'll ever write is the code you delete.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deletion",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-code-youll",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best architecture is the one that doesn't need an architecture diagram.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "architecture",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-architecture-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If your product description needs more than 3 sentences, simplify the product.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business",
        "marketing"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "copywriting",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-your-product-description",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your design system should fit in one file. If it doesn't, you've built a framework.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "design-systems",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 4,
      "spiciness": 3,
      "id": "based-your-design-system-should",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best color palette for a SaaS is your brand color plus gray. Everything else is decoration.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "color",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-color-palette",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best engineers write the fewest lines of code. The worst engineers write the most features.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "efficiency",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-engineers-write",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you can't describe your deployment process in 3 steps, it's too complicated.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "devops"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deployment",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-you-cant-describe",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to improve your code is to delete half of it. Then delete half again.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deletion",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to reduce user confusion is to reduce options. Every choice you give the user is a chance for them to choose wrong.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "users",
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "choices",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your users are smarter than you think. Stop holding their hand. Give them tools and get out of the way.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "users",
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "empowerment",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-users-are-smarter",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your business model should be so simple that a stranger could understand it in 30 seconds. If not, simplify.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "business-model",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-business-model-should",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your SaaS should be so simple that support tickets are the exception, not the rule.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "support",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-saas-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every product should pass the 'Grandma test': could your grandma figure it out? If not, simplify.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "users",
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "usability",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-every-product-should-pass",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication.",
      "author": "Leonardo da Vinci",
      "author_slug": "davinci",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom",
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "classic"
      ],
      "grug_level": 2,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "davinci-simplicity-is-the-ultimate",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Perfection is achieved not when there is nothing more to add, but when there is nothing left to take away.",
