    },
    {
      "text": "The best code is no code at all. The second best code is code that writes itself.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "automation"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-code-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "If your deployment process requires a runbook, it's too complicated. Simplify it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "devops"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "deployment",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-if-your-deployment-process",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to improve your product's design is to remove things, not add them.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "removal",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best SaaS onboarding takes 3 steps or less. If it takes more, simplify the product.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "saas"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "onboarding",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-saas-onboarding",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to prevent bugs is to write simple code. Simple code has fewer places to hide bugs.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "engineering",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "bugs"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your pricing should be a no-brainer. If someone has to think about it, it's too complicated.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "business"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "pricing",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-pricing-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Simplicity is the ultimate form of sophistication.",
      "author": "Leonardo da Vinci",
      "author_slug": "davinci",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "classic"
      ],
      "grug_level": 2,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "davinci-simplicity-is-the-ultimate",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best features are the ones you don't build. Every feature adds maintenance burden.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "features",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-features-are",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your tools should serve you, not the other way around. If a tool adds complexity, replace it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "tools",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-tools-should-serve",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your workflow should be simple enough to explain in 3 steps. If not, simplify it.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "productivity"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "workflow",
        "simplicity"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-workflow-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The art of being wise is the art of knowing what to overlook.",
      "author": "William James",
      "author_slug": "james",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "james-the-art-of-being",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The simplest solution is almost always the best one.",
      "author": "Sherlock Holmes",
      "author_slug": "holmes",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "solutions"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "holmes-the-simplest-solution-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Everything should be made as simple as possible, but not simpler.",
      "author": "Albert Einstein",
      "author_slug": "einstein",
      "categories": [
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "balance"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "einstein-everything-should-be-made",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best design is the simplest one that works.",
      "author": "Albert Einstein",
      "author_slug": "einstein",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "wisdom"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "design"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 1,
      "id": "einstein-the-best-design-is",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Simplicity is not about absence. It's about presence of the right things.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "intention"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-simplicity-is-not-about",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "The best way to simplify is to start with the user's needs, not your features.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "user-needs"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-the-best-way-to",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your product should be so simple that it feels like it was always meant to exist.",
      "author": "based",
      "author_slug": "based",
      "categories": [
        "design",
        "product"
      ],
      "tags": [
        "simplicity",
        "natural"
      ],
      "grug_level": 3,
      "spiciness": 2,
      "id": "based-your-product-should-be",
      "source": "Community sourced"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your indie business should be something you can explain to your parents. If you can't, simplify.",
